    "This aspect is important for our experiments since it suggests that the models are more likely to omit important information for certain languages compared to others, due the the limitation of transformer models in terms of the input length.",
    "Another observation is that the training set is not always representative of the test set.",
    "For example, the articles in the test set for Russian (RU) are twice shorter, on average, than the articles in the training set for this language.",
    "The difference in terms of the input length between training and test data is less significant for sub-task 3, which uses paragraphs as an input, and for which all the inputs are within the limit of transformer models.",
    "We analysed the languages in the training and test sets in terms of the amount of resources."
